20/02/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Economy Minister Anastas Angjeli signed a bilateral investment agreement with UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri on Thursday (19 February).
The accord envisions reciprocal promotion of investments and equal treatment of domestic and foreign investments.
This is the third Kosovo-Albanian co-operation agreement;
the other two were on free trade and eliminating dual taxation.
Angjeli and Holkeri said signing this agreement would boost economic co-operation and development in Kosovo and Albania.
Holkeri added that promoting foreign investment in the Balkans is important, as it extends the bridges of communication between countries.
(ATA, HINA - 19/02/04)
